  "grammarNote": {
    "title": "Possession: avoir",
    "explanation": "Watch for the verb avoir (to have). Avril a un chat. Pops a un labo. The pattern is [person] + a + [thing owned].\n\nNotice how avoir works differently from être: Avril est ici (she IS here) vs. Avril a un chat (she HAS a cat).\n\nRe-read and separate every est from every a. Which describes a state, and which describes ownership?"
